                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1034">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19778</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Collector
                            <persName type="to">Cobb</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-09T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1916, 6, p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Inform British Consul at Chihuahua British Embassy here has received his message
                    regarding situation in Chihuahua City, and desires him to know that inasmuch as
                    the Consul is on the spot, he is the best judge as to what action to take to
                    safeguard British subjects. Department of State wishes British Consul to advise
                    Americans to leave Chihuahua City.</p>
                <p>Endeavor convey foregoing by trustworthy traveler, if possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
